{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Toxoplasma gondii is an obligate intracellular apicomplexan protozoan parasite, with a complex lifestyle involving varied hosts. It has two phases of growth: an intestinal phase in feline hosts, and an extra-intestinal phase in other mammals. Oocysts from an infected cat develop into tachyzoites and, eventually, into bradyzoites and zoitocysts in the extraintestinal host. Transmission of the parasite occurs through contact with infected cats or raw/undercooked meat. In immunocompromised individuals, it can cause severe, often lethal, toxoplasmosis [[cite:PUB00010595]].</p>\n\n<p>Toxoplasma gondii utilise a variety of secretory and antigenic proteins to invade a host and gain access to the intracellular environment. This group represents surface antigen p22 (SAG2) from Toxoplasma gondii [[cite:PUB00068149], [cite:PUB00068150]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR036755", "name" "SRS domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF022996" "Surface antigen 2"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Surface antigen p22", "short" "SAG2"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1, "taxa" 28, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 25, "sets" 0, "proteins" 25, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 25}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR016816", :literature {"PUB00068150" {"URL" nil, "issue" nil, "authors" ["Macedo AG Jr" "Cunha JP Jr" "Cardoso TH" "Silva MV" "Santiago FM" "Silva JS" "Pirovani CP" "Silva DA" "Mineo JR" "Mineo TW."], "ISO_journal" "Parasit Vectors", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1186/1756-3305-6-163", "medline_journal" "Parasit Vectors", "title" "SAG2A protein from Toxoplasma gondii interacts with both innate and adaptive immune compart